                                                                                                                                Input and selection

                                                                                                                                PIN code

                                                                                                                                Partially stable

                                                                                                                                A PIN code (Personal Identification Number) field is commonly used for secure authentication and access control.

                                                                                                                                Usage
                                                                                                                                Specs
                                                                                                                                Status & changelog
                                                                                                                                Common Alternative names
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                PIN, Passcode


                                                                                                                                Questions, comments, feedback?

                                                                                                                                Leave a comment in Figma or reach out to us on Slack.

                                                                                                                                #base-design-support


                                                                                                                                Anatomy

                                                                                                                                PIN code fields follow the same general anatomy of other input types (text field, select, etc.) except for the main container where a user provides the input – instead of using one container, the PIN code field utilizes as many containers as the length of the required code is (also called slots).

                                                                                                                                Slot ranges

                                                                                                                                The length of the PIN code is flexible. Depending on the type of code, it can be anywhere from 4 (minimum) to 8 (maximum) characters.

                                                                                                                                4 (Minimum)
                                                                                                                                8 (Maximum)

                                                                                                                                Usage

                                                                                                                                PIN code fields are often used when a user is asked to provide a string of characters to access their accounts and data and authorize sensitive actions securely.

                                                                                                                                2FA one time PIN code
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                PIN code fields are most commonly used for two-factor authentication during Signup / Login flows, where users receive a temporary code they need to input for added authentication.

                                                                                                                                Account linking PIN code
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                PIN code fields enable users to securely link and verify accounts, devices, or services by entering a code during the linking process, ensuring a secure connection between entities.

                                                                                                                                Trip / Delivery PIN code
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                In Uber's context, another prevalent scenario is using PIN code fields to ensure both the passenger and the driver accurately identify each other, and that the delivery contents reach the customer who ordered them.

                                                                                                                                Masked vs Unmasked

                                                                                                                                Type

                                                                                                                                Use cases

                                                                                                                                Masked

                                                                                                                                Masking PIN code fields (replacing the actual digits with dots) is generally recommended for security reasons, especially in situations where the input is sensitive and private (ex: bank account, card PIN code, etc.)

                                                                                                                                Unmasked

                                                                                                                                In non-sensitive scenarios, plaintext display may be used for clarity and ease of instruction, especially when a user has to manually type in a code (ex: someone verbally dictating a code vs being able to paste it in)

                                                                                                                                Behavior

                                                                                                                                Prototype

                                                                                                                                Unmasked

                                                                                                                                Click on the input to start the prototype. Use your keyboard to type in 1234

                                                                                                                                Masked

                                                                                                                                Click on the input to start the prototype. Use your keyboard to type in 1234

                                                                                                                                States

                                                                                                                                The PIN code field follows all applicable states from the text field component, where applicable.

                                                                                                                                Enabled
                                                                                                                                Active
                                                                                                                                Error
                                                                                                                                Success
                                                                                                                                Incomplete
                                                                                                                                Complete
                                                                                                                                Disabled
                                                                                                                                Read only
                                                                                                                                Hover
                                                                                                                                Pressed
                                                                                                                                Loading

                                                                                                                                Error and Success handling

                                                                                                                                Something important to note is that while PIN code fields do separate the input in multiple containers, they are still treated as a single string of input. What this means for Error and Success states is that you cannot surface either on an individual slot level, only once the input has been filled out.

                                                                                                                                Do
                                                                                                                                Don’t

                                                                                                                                Placeholder value (Unmasked)

                                                                                                                                Similarly to text fields, placeholders are a required part of the PIN code field. We've added some additional logic to aid with displaying a placeholder that always matches the number of slots the field uses.

                                                                                                                                Type

                                                                                                                                Description

                                                                                                                                Example

                                                                                                                                Default placeholder

                                                                                                                                Display when no explicit placeholder is provided (ex: empty string)

                                                                                                                                # of slots: 4

                                                                                                                                placeholder: None

                                                                                                                                displayed: 9999

                                                                                                                                Custom placeholder

                                                                                                                                placeholderLength>=pinCode.length

                                                                                                                                Display the first {n} characters of the placeholder provided, where {n} is the # of slots the field has.

                                                                                                                                # of slots: 4

                                                                                                                                placeholder: 12345

                                                                                                                                displayed: 1234


                                                                                                                                Custom placeholder

                                                                                                                                placeholderLength<pinCode.length


                                                                                                                                Display the characters in a loop, until the entire length of the field has been filled.

                                                                                                                                # of slots: 6

                                                                                                                                placeholder: 1234

                                                                                                                                displayed: 123412


                                                                                                                                # of slots: 4

                                                                                                                                placeholder: A

                                                                                                                                displayed: AAAA

                                                                                                                                Component width

                                                                                                                                The PIN code field is an intrinsic width component, meaning it takes the size of its content. While this works for most use cases, there are scenarios where the combination of slot numbers and selected component size exceeds the available width the device provides.

                                                                                                                                In these cases, we shrink each PIN slot down to fill the available width. Our code components do this automatically, however, you need to manually set the auto layout property to Fill in Figma.
